The paper deals with data detection in large multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. However, based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication and information processing. The paper also mentions wireless systems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of Bayesian approximate message passing (AMP) and state-evolution framework suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
